Package: wolf-database
Architecture: any
Depends:
 ${shlibs:Depends},
 ${misc:Depends},
 postgresql-17,
 postgresql-17-pgvector,
 python3.13,
 python3.13-venv,
 adduser,
Description: Wolf bundled-Postgres component
 wolf-database wraps system-installed PostgreSQL 17 + pgvector with
 Wolf-owned config, data dir, socket, and systemd lifecycle. The
 Postgres binaries come from postgresql-17; this package adds the
 wolf-database CLI + the systemd unit + the dedicated service user
 + FHS-canonical paths under /var/lib/wolf-database/.
 .
 One of three deployable Wolf components per ADR 0016, parallel to
 wolf-server and wolf-dashboard.

Package: wolf-server
Architecture: any
Depends:
 ${shlibs:Depends},
 ${misc:Depends},
 python3.13,
 python3.13-venv,
 adduser,
Description: Wolf agent loop and API service
 wolf-server is the brain component: FastAPI app running the agent
 loop, tool dispatch, organization context enforcement, audit log,
 grounding validator, and the read tools that drive Wazuh queries.
 .
 Connects to wolf-database via DATABASE_URL (asyncpg over TCP). In
 all-in-one installs that's loopback; in distributed deployments
 it's mTLS to wolf-database on a different host.
 .
 Includes the wolf-cert CLI for self-signed CA + leaf certificate
 lifecycle (mTLS substrate per Phase 5.6).

Package: wolf-dashboard
Architecture: any
Depends:
 ${shlibs:Depends},
 ${misc:Depends},
 nodejs (>= 20),
 adduser,
Description: Wolf edge component (Next.js)
 wolf-dashboard is the only Wolf process browsers talk to directly.
 Terminates browser HTTPS, serves the chat UI, reverse-proxies
 /api/v1/* requests to wolf-server over mTLS using the
 dashboard-client cert minted by wolf-cert.
 .
 Built from Next.js 16 with output: "standalone" so production
 doesn't need npm at runtime — just node.

Package: wolf-search
Architecture: all
Depends:
 ${misc:Depends},
 python3-dev,
 python3-babel,
 python3-venv,
 python-is-python3,
 uwsgi,
 uwsgi-plugin-python3,
 git,
 build-essential,
 libxslt-dev,
 zlib1g-dev,
 libffi-dev,
 libssl-dev,
 openssl,
 curl,
 ca-certificates,
Description: Wolf bundled-SearXNG component (loopback metasearch)
 wolf-search wraps a SearXNG metasearch instance installed per the
 official SearXNG Ubuntu/Debian step-by-step docs, pinned to a
 Wolf-verified upstream commit. It is wolf-server's sidecar for the
 web-research tools (ADR 0032): loopback-only on 127.0.0.1:1307,
 called by nothing but wolf-server, no accounts, no API keys, no
 per-query cost.
 .
 The Depends list is the official SearXNG install's apt list —
 postinst executes that exact recipe (git clone at the pinned
 commit + dedicated venv under /usr/local/searxng), so installing
 this package REQUIRES network access to github.com and PyPI.
 Air-gapped installs skip wolf-search (it is a Recommends of the
 wolf meta-package, not a Depends) and use a hosted search backend
 or none.

Package: wolf
Architecture: all
Depends:
 ${misc:Depends},
 wolf-database (= ${binary:Version}),
 wolf-server (= ${binary:Version}),
 wolf-dashboard (= ${binary:Version}),
Recommends:
 wolf-search (= ${binary:Version}),
Description: Wolf — agentic AI for Wazuh (all-in-one meta-package)
 Installs all three core Wolf components on a single host, plus
 wolf-search (SearXNG web research) as a Recommends — installed by
 default, skippable via --no-install-recommends for air-gapped or
 hosted-search-backend deployments. Convenience meta-package for
 the common all-in-one deployment; distributed deployments install
 the individual component packages on each host instead.
 .
 After installation, see /usr/share/doc/wolf/README for the
 one-command bring-up: wolf-database init + wolf-cert init +
 systemctl enable --now wolf-database wolf-server wolf-dashboard.
